	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Flare is a newbie navigation spell, like true north.  Accept Flare when cast will send a light source hurtling through the air or at a designated target.  This is not a dd spell.  It allows you to reveal your location to other who are either trying to find you or whom you are asking for directions.<BR>
<BR>
Fire Flux is an Area effect spell which takes out mobs in your immediate area.  It is considered the last spell cast by a mage who couldn't get out of a bad situation and simply wants to make the mob pay for killing him.  Or sometimes it can be used with limmited success against a mob contained in a small area by a group of tanks or walls and such.<BR>
<BR>
Whisp, is simply a summoned light source which when worn in one of your general cargo slots, those that appear in your inventory screen but are not inside a container of any type, creates a source of light which the mage can use as if it were a torch or lantern.<BR>
<BR>
Kelemvory Trueheart<BR>
45 LVL Magician<BR>
Povar Server.<BR>
<BR>
PS.  I am going to have to agree that mages need a little tweaking.  Overall, we are a good class, but there are things that we should be able to do but can't because of how sony/verant is trying to &quot;equalize the classes.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
PPS.  Any class can exploit, in one way or another, the attributes of thier class, but to do that with a mage is considerably difficult.  hehe plus we seem to be absent-minded summoners.  hheeh, its like, oh here is a sword, well here ya go pet, whoa, hey looky there, throwing stars, here ya rogue/shaman, who look arrows, gee sure wish I could use a bow.  It is kind of funny when you think about it.  I would say that if they are going to allow us to summon weapons for other classes to use, then allow us to summon weapons that another class member, of equal lvl to ours can use.  I don't mind helping out low lvl rogues or tanks with summoned weaponry, but it is just that, the way the zones are made, it is not like a 45th lvl magician is going to be in the same zone as a 10 lvl warrior.  At least not very often or for an extended period of time.  <BR>
<BR>
Just my two cps.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
