	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Nope I am going to have to agree with the guy who is realistic about mages.  All of our shielding spells are overwritten by either Shaman or Cleric buffs and well.  Asside from Boon of Imoliation we don't get group buff spells till well into the later 50s.<BR>
<BR>
What he says about the pets is true too.  No other class is penalized for their pets, when their pets do more than half.  And guys look at what he is saying in total.  Our spells get resisted more, our magic resistence lowering thing is resisted almost constantly.  This might not seem like much of a problem but you try to fight Aviak Avocets at lvl 25, they con blue yet your magic doesn't work on them amost at all.  You basically have to Fire Shield your pet and send him in and either constantly heal your pet with this worthless renew elements or, I beleive summoning, which comes much later and is quite worthless for our later pets, or you have to chain cast pets, and hope you don't get hit while trying to.<BR>
<BR>
I am going to have to agree with him about our spells getting farmed out too.  What is the point in having a line of spells for the conjuration masters if it is only going to be given to mele folks by way of thier boots, pants, and whatever verant wants to put an effect on.<BR>
<BR>
Look at our higher robes and such, we get shield of lava which is NICE don't get me wrong but it is a spell that is in our own line.  We are able to cast it when we get lvl 49 and as such you can't get the robe till 50 unless somebody is either powerlvling you or out right twinking ya.  I would have to say that not much thought when into mages, or rounding them out so they would be as desireable as say, and enchanter or shaman or druid or cleric.  <BR>
<BR>
And don't get me started about Call of the Hero!  That spell is near impossible to get and it only works if the person you are trying to save is in the same zone.  For pete sake the guy is in your party, let the spell be party specific if anything, and let it be castable if say, you friend either died and needs a quick port back to the corpse or if they went to sell and got jumped and needed help.  That would be a way of improving the need for magicians.  Verant, you might want to think about that.<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

